quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
  12,97,"They said: "
  12,98,"He said: "
  12,99,"Then, when they came in before Yûsuf (Joseph), he took his parents to himself and said: "
  14,43,"(They will be) hastening forward with necks outstretched, their heads raised up (towards the sky), their gaze returning not towards them and their hearts empty (from thinking because of extreme fear)."
  14,44,"And warn (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه و سلم) mankind of the Day when the torment will come unto them; then the wrong-doers will say: "
  14,45,""
  15,16,"And indeed, We have put the big stars in the heaven and We beautified it for the beholders.{1}",footnotes:1:[{15:16} See the footnote of {6:97}.]
  15,17,"And We have guarded it (near heaven) from every outcast Shaitân (devil)."
  15,18,"Except him (devil) who steals the hearing then he is pursued by a clear flaming fire."